| 1 | Design SOM node hierarchy | Branch ownership, read-access permissions, single-copy architecture per the architecture doc (Section 9) |
| 2 | Implement `som/` module with `sneeze::som` namespace | Core node types: spatial node, geometry node, light node, group node |
| 3 | Refactor renderer to consume SOM rather than raw sphere/curve lists | Renderer walks the SOM tree instead of receiving flat data from main.cpp |
| 4 | Refactor astro module to populate SOM nodes | Bodies write into the SOM; main.cpp no longer manually bridges astro to renderer |
| 5 | Multi-source branch architecture | SOM branches owned by different sources (local astro vs. future fabric services) |
| 6 | SOM change detection / dirty flagging | Only re-submit changed geometry to ANARI, not the entire scene every frame |

